1
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:07,760
- Hey. - Hi.

2
00:00:07,810 --> 00:00:09,100
Pheebs, what's wrong?

3
00:00:09,150 --> 00:00:11,190
I'm just so exhausted from dragging around

4
00:00:11,240 --> 00:00:12,960
this huge engagement ring.

5
00:00:13,090 --> 00:00:14,490
Oh, my God.

6
00:00:14,550 --> 00:00:15,850
Congratulations.

7
00:00:16,020 --> 00:00:17,630
So did he get on one knee?

8
00:00:17,680 --> 00:00:19,340
Did he have a speech prepared?

9
00:00:19,390 --> 00:00:20,990
Oh, did he cry?

10
00:00:23,170 --> 00:00:25,810
Yeah, big surprise, I like proposals.

11
00:00:27,250 --> 00:00:29,030
Well, it was really sweet,

12
00:00:29,080 --> 00:00:31,270
and, like, the most romantic thing ever.

13
00:00:31,320 --> 00:00:33,020
Here's to Phoebe,

14
00:00:33,070 --> 00:00:34,860
who's found the greatest guy in the world.

15
00:00:34,910 --> 00:00:36,070
To Phoebe and--

16
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:37,810
I want to say "Mike"?

17
00:00:39,060 --> 00:00:40,300
To Phoebe and Mike.

18
00:00:41,420 --> 00:00:42,550
Thank you.

19
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:44,280
Oh, and I have something for you.

20
00:00:44,760 --> 00:00:46,290
It's my little black book.

21
00:00:46,340 --> 00:00:48,240
It's got the numbers of all the guys I've dated.

22
00:00:48,290 --> 00:00:51,630
Oh, Phoebe, that's nice,

23
00:00:51,680 --> 00:00:52,940
but you know what? I think I'm okay.

24
00:00:52,990 --> 00:00:53,820
Why don't you just give it

25
00:00:53,870 --> 00:00:55,230
to one of your other single girlfriends.

26
00:00:55,280 --> 00:00:57,110
I would, but you're the last one.

27
00:00:59,530 --> 00:01:00,540
Give me the book!

28
00:01:02,570 --> 00:01:04,340
"Pablo Diaz.

29
00:01:04,390 --> 00:01:06,170
Brady Smith.

30
00:01:07,310 --> 00:01:09,100
Guy in Van"?

31
00:01:09,150 --> 00:01:10,700
Oh, my first love.

32
00:01:12,380 --> 00:01:14,270
What is the red X next to

33
00:01:14,270 --> 00:01:15,810
Bob Gremore's name mean?

34
00:01:15,860 --> 00:01:16,790
Dead.

35
00:01:19,010 --> 00:01:21,790
Oh, it's okay. No, he was old. Yeah.

36
00:01:22,350 --> 00:01:23,400
And he lived a full life.

37
00:01:23,450 --> 00:01:25,810
He was in the first wave at Omaha Beach.

38
00:01:23,450 --> 00:01:25,810
Omaha Beach:1944年诺曼底登陆中美军负责的一段

39
00:01:27,260 --> 00:01:29,250
oh, I'm sorry. I should've given you guys my black book

40
00:01:29,300 --> 00:01:30,480
when I got married.

41
00:01:30,530 --> 00:01:31,650
Although, it wasn't so much a book

42
00:01:31,700 --> 00:01:33,040
as a napkin.

43
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:36,660
With Janice's phone number on it.

44
00:01:37,710 --> 00:01:40,730
Phoebe, isn't Jethro Tull a band?

45
00:01:45,030 --> 00:01:46,490
Oh, yes, they are.

46
00:01:48,260 --> 00:01:50,490
《老友记》第十季第六集 罗斯的科研补助金

47
00:02:27,930 --> 00:02:28,960
Hey, honey.

48
00:02:30,180 --> 00:02:31,190
Hey, sweetie.

49
00:02:32,390 --> 00:02:33,710
- Is Monica not here? - No.

50
00:02:33,980 --> 00:02:35,250
Then I'll tell you.

51
00:02:35,300 --> 00:02:38,030
My agency was bidding for a big account, and they got it.

52
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:39,730
It's my first national commercial.

53
00:02:39,780 --> 00:02:40,550
Cool.

54
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:41,580
And I don't want to brag,

55
00:02:41,630 --> 00:02:43,370
but a lot of the ideas were mine.

56
00:02:43,900 --> 00:02:45,080
Hell, you weren't there.

57
00:02:45,130 --> 00:02:46,470
All the ideas were mine.

58
00:02:47,140 --> 00:02:48,470
That's great.

59
00:02:48,520 --> 00:02:50,760
Hey, can you cast me in it?

60
00:02:51,430 --> 00:02:54,000
I really don't think you're right for the part.

61
00:02:54,050 --> 00:02:55,570
What do you mean? I can do anything.

62
00:02:55,620 --> 00:02:57,130
I'm a chameleon.

63
00:02:59,130 --> 00:03:00,420
I'm old.

64
00:03:02,540 --> 00:03:03,950
I'm tired.

65
00:03:04,860 --> 00:03:06,950
Oh, I am hot. I'm cold.

66
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:09,250
Come on, what can't I do?

67
00:03:10,420 --> 00:03:12,570
First of all, bravo.

68
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:15,570
But I don't think you're right for this.

69
00:03:15,620 --> 00:03:17,840
The part's a stuffy college professor.

70
00:03:17,890 --> 00:03:19,310
I can do that.

71
00:03:19,530 --> 00:03:21,800
Hello, I'm your professor.

72
00:03:22,050 --> 00:03:24,210
When I'm not busy thinking of important things,

73
00:03:24,260 --> 00:03:26,470
or professing...

74
00:03:27,580 --> 00:03:29,890
...l like to use-- What's the product?

75
00:03:30,090 --> 00:03:33,600
Software that facilitates inter-business networking e-solutions.

76
00:03:38,770 --> 00:03:40,080
I'm cold.

77
00:03:43,150 --> 00:03:44,450
- Hey. - Hey.

78
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:45,580
Guess who's a finalist

79
00:03:45,630 --> 00:03:47,650
for a huge research grant?

80
00:03:47,700 --> 00:03:48,640
I'll give you a hint.

81
00:03:48,690 --> 00:03:49,810
He's looking right at you.

82
00:03:51,040 --> 00:03:52,800
Well, unless it's the creepy guy

83
00:03:52,850 --> 00:03:54,390
with his hand up his kilt...

84
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:56,290
...I'm gonna say, "Congratulations."

85
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:58,460
I'm so excited.

86
00:03:58,510 --> 00:04:01,830
Apparently, I beat out hundreds of other applicants...

87
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:04,660
...including five guys I went to graduate school with.

88
00:04:04,710 --> 00:04:07,470
Not that I'm keeping score, or anything. Five.

89
00:04:08,500 --> 00:04:10,340
- Wow, that's great. - Yeah.

90
00:04:10,390 --> 00:04:11,430
So tell me about the grant.

91
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:13,490
Well, okay, it's for $25,000.

92
00:04:13,630 --> 00:04:14,670
And if I get it,

93
00:04:14,670 --> 00:04:17,140
I'll be able to complete my field research.

94
00:04:17,190 --> 00:04:19,190
And there will be an article about me

95
00:04:19,240 --> 00:04:21,140
in the <i>Paleontology Review</i>.

96
00:04:21,190 --> 00:04:23,370
It'll be the first time my name is in there...

97
00:04:23,420 --> 00:04:26,060
...without people raising serious questions about my work.

98
00:04:27,540 --> 00:04:29,810
Are you talking about the Dewer Grant?

99
00:04:29,860 --> 00:04:30,820
Yeah. Why?

100
00:04:30,870 --> 00:04:33,160
Benjamin Hobart is administering that grant.

101
00:04:33,210 --> 00:04:35,360
- Your ex-boyfriend? - Yeah.

102
00:04:35,410 --> 00:04:37,680
So your ex-boyfriend is gonna determine

103
00:04:37,730 --> 00:04:40,000
if your new boyfriend gets this grant?

104
00:04:40,050 --> 00:04:42,070
Wow, your new boyfriend is screwed.

105
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:45,680
No. No, we ended on great terms.

106
00:04:45,730 --> 00:04:46,440
I mean if anything,

107
00:04:46,490 --> 00:04:47,680
I think this could help you. You know what?

108
00:04:47,730 --> 00:04:50,040
Why don't we all go out to dinner,

109
00:04:50,090 --> 00:04:51,310
and I can introduce you.

110
00:04:51,730 --> 00:04:52,960
If you think it'd help.

111
00:04:53,010 --> 00:04:54,710
Yeah, absolutely. I'll call him.

112
00:04:54,760 --> 00:04:57,630
Now, is there anything I could do to butter him up?

113
00:04:57,680 --> 00:04:59,390
Anything he really likes?

114
00:05:00,770 --> 00:05:02,880
He does have a pretty serious latex fetish.

115
00:05:02,930 --> 00:05:04,480
We'll see how dinner goes.

116
00:05:09,550 --> 00:05:11,760
- Hey. - Hey, you want to go see a movie?

117
00:05:12,550 --> 00:05:14,910
I told you I had to spend all day clearing out stuff

118
00:05:14,960 --> 00:05:16,160
so Mike could move in.

119
00:05:16,210 --> 00:05:17,780
- Oh, right. - Yeah.

120
00:05:17,830 --> 00:05:19,890
Now that I'm here,

121
00:05:19,940 --> 00:05:22,290
I might as well help with the cleaning and organizing.

122
00:05:22,340 --> 00:05:24,750
I just happen to have my label maker.

123
00:05:26,460 --> 00:05:29,040
Oh, it's so hard to get rid of stuff.

124
00:05:29,090 --> 00:05:31,050
Did you and Chandler make compromises

125
00:05:31,100 --> 00:05:32,510
when you moved in together?

126
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:34,050
Chandler did.

127
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:36,640
What does he want you to give up?

128
00:05:36,690 --> 00:05:37,800
A bunch of stuff.

129
00:05:37,850 --> 00:05:39,190
And the worst one,

130
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:41,140
he wants me to get rid of Gladys.

131
00:05:41,420 --> 00:05:42,840
Who's Gladys?

132
00:05:47,140 --> 00:05:48,860
What a tragic loss.

133
00:05:49,910 --> 00:05:52,050
Yeah, I really hate to give her up.

134
00:05:52,370 --> 00:05:54,490
Oh, I know. Oh, you should take her.

135
00:05:57,230 --> 00:05:59,680
I don't know.

136
00:06:00,520 --> 00:06:02,290
What, you don't like her?

137
00:06:02,340 --> 00:06:05,790
Of course I do. What's not to like?

138
00:06:06,900 --> 00:06:08,320
I'd take her in a minute.

139
00:06:09,340 --> 00:06:11,520
But I think that you're giving up too easy.

140
00:06:11,570 --> 00:06:13,830
Honey, I think that you need to fight for her.

141
00:06:15,070 --> 00:06:17,190
- Really, you think? - Absolutely.

142
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:18,460
You say to him,

143
00:06:18,510 --> 00:06:20,480
"I'm sorry, Mike, I can't live without her.

144
00:06:20,530 --> 00:06:22,400
She means too much to me."

145
00:06:23,150 --> 00:06:25,980
Okay, I'll fight for her. Okay.

146
00:06:26,740 --> 00:06:29,000
Oh, wait. I just realized, if I do that,

147
00:06:29,050 --> 00:06:30,270
that means you don't get her.

148
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:32,380
Damn it, I did not think this through.

149
00:06:36,430 --> 00:06:38,390
- Hey, guys. - Hey.

150
00:06:38,390 --> 00:06:40,290
Oh, any word on casting yet?

151
00:06:40,340 --> 00:06:42,460
I told you, you're not right for the part.

152
00:06:42,510 --> 00:06:43,670
What do you mean?

153
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:45,400
Rach, don't I seem like a professor

154
00:06:45,450 --> 00:06:47,610
you'd buy some kind of e-crap from?

155
00:06:48,890 --> 00:06:49,680
I'm sorry,

156
00:06:49,730 --> 00:06:51,940
this sounds like something I'm never gonna be interested in.

157
00:06:53,100 --> 00:06:54,860
Look, come on, please?

158
00:06:54,910 --> 00:06:57,740
It's not like I'm asking you for some crazy favor.

159
00:06:57,900 --> 00:06:58,960
This is what I do for a living.

160
00:06:59,010 --> 00:07:00,770
I am a professional actor.

161
00:07:00,820 --> 00:07:02,900
Man, I'm two hours late for work.

162
00:07:04,660 --> 00:07:06,090
Here's a copy of my reel.

163
00:07:06,140 --> 00:07:07,970
It's got all the commercials that I've been in.

164
00:07:08,020 --> 00:07:09,830
- Joe-- - Just watch it.

165
00:07:09,880 --> 00:07:10,710
If you don't like it,

166
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:12,730
don't pass it on to your bosses.

167
00:07:13,030 --> 00:07:15,020
- Fine. - Thank you.

168
00:07:19,670 --> 00:07:22,060
- Work, Joe. - Damn it.

169
00:07:25,700 --> 00:07:27,010
What am I gonna do now?

170
00:07:27,060 --> 00:07:28,330
Just pass the tape along.

171
00:07:28,380 --> 00:07:30,110
He's not right for the part.

172
00:07:30,160 --> 00:07:31,070
If I suggest him,

173
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:32,820
my bosses will think I'm an idiot.

174
00:07:32,870 --> 00:07:35,050
And that's something they should learn on their own.

175
00:07:35,780 --> 00:07:38,060
Just tell Joey that you watched the tape...

176
00:07:38,110 --> 00:07:40,230
...and you liked it, but your bosses didn't.

177
00:07:40,280 --> 00:07:41,560
Then that way, you're the good guy,

178
00:07:41,610 --> 00:07:42,920
and they're the bad guy.

179
00:07:42,970 --> 00:07:45,450
That's good. I liked it, they didn't.

180
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:50,510
Joey, for God's sake, go to work.

181
00:07:55,630 --> 00:07:58,820
I can't believe I'm about to meet Benjamin Hobart.

182
00:07:58,870 --> 00:08:00,940
I've always thought of him as someone I'd invite...

183
00:08:00,990 --> 00:08:03,720
...to my fantasy dinner party.

184
00:08:04,850 --> 00:08:05,930
Do you think there's any chance

185
00:08:05,980 --> 00:08:08,330
he'll bring Christie Brinkley or C-3PO?

186
00:08:10,190 --> 00:08:12,380
Sorry, it looks like it's just him.

187
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:15,680
Charlie.

188
00:08:18,140 --> 00:08:22,220
My God, you look absolutely stunning.

189
00:08:22,270 --> 00:08:25,240
Well, I am having a good hair day.

190
00:08:26,260 --> 00:08:29,480
- It's so good to see you. - Oh, you too.

191
00:08:33,460 --> 00:08:34,760
I'm okay.

192
00:08:35,980 --> 00:08:39,030
I'm sorry. Ross Geller, Benjamin Hobart.

193
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:40,770
It's an honor to meet you.

194
00:08:40,820 --> 00:08:42,920
I can't tell you how long...

195
00:08:42,970 --> 00:08:47,220
...I've been an admirer of your work. I mean, that Nobel Prize.

196
00:08:49,070 --> 00:08:50,840
I mean, I have to tell you

197
00:08:50,890 --> 00:08:53,580
that you're one of the reasons I got into the field.

198
00:08:53,930 --> 00:08:55,610
Well, likewise.

199
00:08:56,180 --> 00:08:58,020
Actually not likewise.

200
00:08:58,070 --> 00:08:59,770
I'd never heard of you until this morning.

201
00:08:59,820 --> 00:09:01,540
But it's nice to be nice.

202
00:09:03,420 --> 00:09:06,260
- Shall we? - Yeah. Thank you.

203
00:09:09,740 --> 00:09:12,840
I can't believe that you chose this restaurant.

204
00:09:13,430 --> 00:09:14,670
Do you remember the night?

205
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:17,280
Oh, my God. I completely forgot.

206
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:22,330
Oh, my God, I can't believe they let us back in this place.

207
00:09:30,020 --> 00:09:31,460
You weren't there.

208
00:09:32,950 --> 00:09:36,260
No, but, you know, it's just a funny image.

209
00:09:36,310 --> 00:09:40,940
You know, the two of you in this restaurant with the....

210
00:09:43,330 --> 00:09:45,520
Ross, why don't you tell Benji

211
00:09:45,570 --> 00:09:47,830
about your proposal while I go to the ladies' room.

212
00:09:50,260 --> 00:09:52,170
So tell me about it.

213
00:09:52,220 --> 00:09:56,470
Painted Desert:在亚利桑那州北部

214
00:09:52,220 --> 00:09:56,470
Okay. Well, I would like to do a dig in the Painted Desert.

215
00:09:56,520 --> 00:10:00,180
There are still several areas that haven't been fully excavated.

216
00:10:00,230 --> 00:10:01,540
- Break up with Charlie. - What?

217
00:10:01,590 --> 00:10:02,310
What?

218
00:10:04,140 --> 00:10:08,400
Did you just say, "Break up with Charlie"?

219
00:10:09,430 --> 00:10:11,050
Well, yes and no.

220
00:10:11,100 --> 00:10:14,030
Yes, I did say it. And no, I didn't not say it.

221
00:10:15,630 --> 00:10:17,860
Kind of inappropriate, don't you think?

222
00:10:17,910 --> 00:10:19,830
Listen, I'm sorry.

223
00:10:19,880 --> 00:10:21,250
I just haven't seen her for so long,

224
00:10:21,300 --> 00:10:23,370
all these feelings are rushing back.

225
00:10:23,420 --> 00:10:24,390
I'm starting to realize

226
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:26,060
how much I've missed her.

227
00:10:26,110 --> 00:10:28,420
And I'm gonna need you to break up with her.

228
00:10:30,560 --> 00:10:32,110
Are you serious?

229
00:10:32,160 --> 00:10:33,550
If you say, yes, then I'm serious.

230
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:35,410
If you say, no, then I'm joking.

231
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:38,960
- No. - Joking it is.

232
00:10:43,270 --> 00:10:44,720
Hi, sorry I'm late.

233
00:10:44,770 --> 00:10:46,180
Hey, how'd it go with Mike?

234
00:10:46,230 --> 00:10:47,600
Is he gonna let you keep the painting?

235
00:10:47,650 --> 00:10:49,990
No, he really hates it.

236
00:10:50,250 --> 00:10:53,060
But he's gonna let me keep my box of human hair.

237
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:56,440
So you gotta pick your battles.

238
00:10:56,950 --> 00:10:59,850
But the good news is, Gladys is yours.

239
00:11:01,650 --> 00:11:03,390
Wow, what's the bad news?

240
00:11:04,570 --> 00:11:05,710
Who's Gladys?

241
00:11:05,830 --> 00:11:07,920
Oh, she's that work of art I made.

242
00:11:07,970 --> 00:11:10,200
You know, with the woman coming out of the frame.

243
00:11:11,080 --> 00:11:14,510
And Monica gets to keep her?

244
00:11:15,490 --> 00:11:18,800
In her house? I am so jealous.

245
00:11:20,530 --> 00:11:22,770
I didn't know you wanted her too.

246
00:11:24,780 --> 00:11:27,650
Well, I mean, sure, of course.

247
00:11:28,730 --> 00:11:31,030
But you already gave that to Monica, so....

248
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:33,200
You know, I would give her up for you.

249
00:11:33,250 --> 00:11:34,750
No, I couldn't let you do that.

250
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:37,330
- No, but I want to. - But I don't want you to.

251
00:11:37,380 --> 00:11:41,470
- But I insist. - But I insist harder.

252
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:45,740
Girls. Girls. Stop. Okay, we'll flip a coin.

253
00:11:45,790 --> 00:11:46,750
Heads, she's Rachel's.

254
00:11:46,800 --> 00:11:48,090
Tails, she's Monica's.

255
00:11:51,380 --> 00:11:53,200
Tails. Monica, she's yours.

256
00:11:53,250 --> 00:11:55,200
No, that landed in your food.

257
00:11:56,280 --> 00:11:57,370
No, no, that's okay.

258
00:11:57,420 --> 00:11:59,810
You won fair and square. I'm so sad.

259
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:04,780
Hey, Joe?

260
00:12:04,780 --> 00:12:06,510
- What's up? - Bad news.

261
00:12:06,510 --> 00:12:07,370
I watched the tape

262
00:12:07,370 --> 00:12:08,730
and passed it along to my bosses

263
00:12:08,730 --> 00:12:10,460
and they weren't interested.

264
00:12:12,350 --> 00:12:13,780
I'm sorry, man.

265
00:12:16,310 --> 00:12:18,170
But you watched the tape?

266
00:12:18,220 --> 00:12:20,490
Yeah, I liked it.

267
